    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, make a well in the centre of the pan and crack the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into it</p><p>Break the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> up with a spatula then allow to set slightly before mixing it through the rice</p><p>Remove the<strong> </strong>pan from the heat and fluff the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a fork</p><p>Stir through the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) – this is your <strong>fragrant Thai-style rice</strong></p>",
